chunk: Cheesy English muffins and cucumber sticks recipe Toasted English muffins with a tasty layer of cream cheese and cucumber sticks on the side – a perfect mid-afternoon snack for your baby. Age: 12 months and older Prep: 5 mins Cook: 2 mins Portions: 2 Ingredients - 4 thick cucumber finger sticks, washed and halved lengthways - 1 English muffin, halved - 30g full-fat cream cheese Method Toast or grill the muffin until golden brown, then spread the cream cheese evenly. Serve with the cucumber sticks. Any leftover cucumber will make a great snack for older children and other members of the family too. Information: Try your baby with some different vegetables such as carrot, pepper or celery sticks on the side. Or why not mix it up with a couple of sticks of each.
